                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(1)\">I shall take the earliest oppor<lb/>tunity to lay the invitation\n                before my<lb/> Board of Trustees the result of which<lb/> I trust will be\n                satisfactory and which<lb/> I shall take pleasure to communicate</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Mrs Lyons</persName> joins with me in<lb/> kind regards to\n                yourself and Lady<lb/> She intends, God willing to avail her<lb/>-self of this\n                opportunity to visit<lb/>\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> when she will personally<lb/> make her\n                acknowledgments for your kind<lb/> remembrance of her wishes.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I remain with due respect</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">My Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Yours very truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">J I Lyons</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Abm Hart Esqr</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3jw8773f/canvas/p2"
